Key Match Events: Adolis Garcia hit a line-drive grand slam in the top of the ninth inning to secure the Rangers' victory.
Mitch Garver had three hits, including a key solo home run and an RBI double.
Jonah Heim hit a two-run home run off Framber Valdez.
Nathan Eovaldi allowed just two runs on five hits over 6.1 innings.
Josh Sborz and Jose Leclerc worked into and out of jams to preserve the lead.
Yordan Álvarez had an RBI single in the top of the first inning.
Mauricio Dubón hit a sacrifice fly to bring home Yordan Álvarez in the sixth inning.
Hector Neris got Corey Seager to ground out in the top of the seventh with two runners on.
Josh Sborz got Michael Brantley to ground into a double play in the bottom of the seventh.
Bryan Abreu struck out Adolis Garcia in the rematch after their Game 5 incident.
Jose Leclerc walked Kyle Tucker to load the bases but got Jon Singleton swinging to preserve the Rangers' lead.
Ryne Stanek hit Corey Seager with a pitch to give the Rangers their fifth run.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Texas Rangers continued the 'road-field advantage' trend of this ALCS.
Astros fans expressed their displeasure over Bryan Abreu's pending two-game suspension for hitting Adolis Garcia in Game 5.
